<Content>Cool hotel, excellent location My wife and I have just returned from four days at Hotel Regina Barcelona, which we chose on the strength of the reviews here, we were not disappointed !We have both been to Barcelona several times before so we knew the area, the hotel is in an excellent location just of Catalunya Sq, 5 mins from La Rambla. Don鈥檛 get a cab from the airport, take the bus it鈥檚 4 Euros from the airport and runs every 10 mins and stops in Catalunya Sq, get of the bus look across the square for the BBVA clock and Habitat, the hotel in 2 mins walk across the square between the two buildings.We were in Barcelona for my birthday, we booked a superior room and requested a high floor room with street view. We arrived at 11am expecting to be told you can leave your bags as the room is not ready, not so, checked in OK as the room was ready (I would not expect this though, as the time we went was a quiet one) upstairs to rm 405 鈥?high floor, street view !! 5 mins later their was a knock at the door, a bottle of Cava and two glasses with a birthday wish compliments of the hotel !Our room was large, clean, bright and airy it felt more like we were in an apartment than a hotel room, the only slight disappointment was that we had two single beds pushed together to make a double rather than just a double, but it was very comfy all the same. Some people have commented about train noise etc. We didn鈥檛 experience any of this, in fact once the balcony doors were shut outside traffic noise etc was virtually non existent. All areas of the hotel we found were clean and tidy at all times. The hotel bar (at the time we were their) was quiet, I would recommend the cocktail bar at the Pullitzer next door (part of the same group)I stay away through work quite often and make a point of avoiding eating in any of the hotels I stay in. My wife commented on how whenever we go away the first nights meal is always the worst as you never know where to go and are just to tired to bother. If you have dinner at the Pullitzer next door on the first night I guarantee you will not be disappointed, the food is superb. We didn鈥檛 have breakfast at the hotel 鈥?got up to late ! I鈥檇 avoid the diner/restaurant across the road (rude  surly staff) Starbucks is 20 yards left out of the hotel.The last time we were in Barcelona we had lunch at one of the many outside eateries on the Ramblas, my advice avoid this overpriced tourist fare, go into the market on the Ramblas and head for the 鈥榚at at bars鈥?at the back the food is cooked fresh while you wait in front of you and is very good. Whilst we are talking about food L鈥?Olivia (left out of the hotel, cross the road and up the passage between the shops) is very good. I would definitely avoid Les Quinze Nits in Placa Reial just of the Ramblas, we queued for an hour to be served tasteless food and when we complained the manager said 鈥榟ow do we know what it should taste like鈥?!! with your back to Les Quinze look to the left corner of the square and go to Santa Monica, good food, great staff.If you go down to the marina/Port Vell, Luz de Gas (the blue boat) is a must, the atmosphere and the tapas is excellent though you will have to queue if the sun is out ! but once you have sat down your table is yours to soak up the sun and atmosphere for as long as you want it. If however the queue is to long walk past Luz de Gas to the history museum, take the lift to the 4th floor (entry is free) the caf茅 serves superb food and if it鈥檚 sunny you can eat the superb food on the terrace with excellent views over the marina.Anyway back to Regina, great hotel, great location excellent staff for who nothing seems too much trouble I would recommend it all day long, in fact we are going back in June !! 
