<Content>Average Hotel in a Brilliant Location My wife and I stayed at the Hotel Regina for 4 nights over Xmas and found it to be an excellent hotel in terms of location. It was a good base to start our busy sightseeing schedule being within easy access to the Bus Turistic, the Metro and the Aerobus (we used the latter to and from the airport).The room we had (508) had a balcony but was far from soundproof as we woken up by our neighbours singing in the shower each morning. The breakfast was very generous albeit monotonous. The staff were friendly with a few exceptions who found it difficult to smile. You could also feel the rumble of the Metro underground although this wasn't such a big deal. The rooms were on the small side but sufficient and the decor more on the modest side. All in all it's an average hotel with its key advantages being the complimentary breakfast, excellent location and the convenience of dealing with a familiar hotel group (ie Best Western). The latter was an advantage when I was chasing up some anomalies in my credit card charges - I got excellent feedback from the Best Western Customer Care team. 
