<Content>A good deal for 90 Euros We stayed at the Best western Regina for 4 nights during Christmas. We booked it for 90 Euros which we felt was a good deal for the location (and our budget). The location is excellent. The room was very clean, but on the small size. The staff was very friendly and even recommended some nice restaurants to eat in, which we did. Buffet breakfast was included. It was great the first few mornings, but after a while we got sick of the same things(eggs, ham, pastries) however it was all very fresh and good quality. The rooms are not soundproof and we could hear the people in the next room showering and that sounded like the street cleaners were out! We thought we could also hear pigeons(we were on the top floor) and the room had a balcony. Our room -509, did have a good view.There was access to a complimentary gym, which was good and about 5 blocks away. Would have liked to have one onsite though. The wireless internet was not working very well in room, so we went downstairs where it worked perfectly. The last night we were there I ordered a glass of milk and it cost 2 euros 50! Highway robbery -a Heineken was only 3 Euros!!!We had to extend out stay by two nights, and the price went up by 60 Euros. They would not let us keep the room for 90 Euros, so we decided to go next door to the Hotel Pulitzer, which was only 140 including breakfast. It was a more modern hotel with larger room, very chic and clean looking. Check our review. 
