<Content>Excellent hotel I visited here with three of my girl friends for 4 nights in June, and everything I have to say about it is good! The staff were extremely helpful by providing a secure room for our luggage after we had checked out, directing us to the nearest bank to exchange travellers cheques, and booking taxis etc.The room itself was lovely, ours was situated on the front of the building with a private (but small!) balcony, overlooking the main street and Placa Catalunya at the end. The decor was modern with plain white walls, brown wooden floors and brown leather armchairs. The bathroom was spotless and modern. The location of the hotel was excellent, it was very close to Placa Catalunya, without the noise associated with such a busy square. This allowed us to use the metro, buses and tourist buses very easily. The breakfast had a lot to choose from, fresh pastries, fresh fruit, cereals along with continental breakfasts such as cheeses and meats. Definitely worth the money!As for the city, Barcelona is beautiful, and there is so much to see - I didn't get to see everything I wanted to, so I'll just have to go back! I wouldn't recommend the tourist bus in the height of summer, as we often found it was a scramble for the top deck when it was sunny, and the metro is a lot easier and cheaper to use (4.80 euros for a day pass compared with 21 euros for two day tourist bus pass). 
